.TH "rdma_find_gid" 9 "rdma_find_gid" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
rdma_find_gid \- Returns SGID attributes if the matching GID is found.
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "const struct ib_gid_attr *" rdma_find_gid
.BI "(struct ib_device *device "  ","
.BI "const union ib_gid *gid "  ","
.BI "enum ib_gid_type gid_type "  ","
.BI "struct net_device *ndev "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "device" 12
The device to query.
.IP "gid" 12
The GID value to search for.
.IP "gid_type" 12
The GID type to search for.
.IP "ndev" 12
In RoCE, the net device of the device. NULL means ignore.
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
\fBrdma_find_gid\fP searches for the specified GID value in the software cache.

Returns GID attributes if a valid GID is found or returns ERR_PTR for the
error. The caller must invoke \fBrdma_put_gid_attr\fP to release the reference.
